What you need to know:

The petitioners, including the National Assembly and Senate, lawyer Kamotho Njenga and two voters — Leina Konchellah and Mohsen Munasar — are opposed to the decision of Justice Mwilu to appoint the bench, a duty that is reserved for the CJ.They argued that the office of the Deputy Chief Justice cannot exercise administrative powers conferred on the Chief Justice under the Constitution.Justice Mwilu appointed Justice Lydia Achode as the chair of the Bench whose members include Justices George Odunga, James Makau, Anthony Ndung’u and Pauline Nyamweya.